   Schedule an Appointment        Schedule an Appointment  We realize a lot of changes have transpired over the last few weeks due to COVID-19. We want to let you know that the Engineering Career Center is here to help you!  Since the Engineering Career Center is currently closed, we are now providing virtual advising services:   Zoom, Hangout, and/or Email Career Advising Services Available! You will still need to make an appointment online on UICcareers.com for advising.   Please make sure to detail your preferred email and phone number in the appointment request notes.  You will receive an email notification once the career advisor approves your appointment time.  Your career advisor will then send you a link to access your appointment call over Google Hangouts or Zoom. Dial-in options are available if you do not have access to a computer at this time.    Alumni can still make appointments via UICCareers.com for several months after graduation. If you no longer have access to your UICcareers.com account, please email the advisor designated for your major. Click here to see a list of advisors by major.  Quick Questions that can be handled over email: please email one of us !  Our website has wonderful resources available 24/7, so please take advantage! Find job search boards online, tips for LinkedIn, practice interview questions, and more in the “Career Tools” tab!  Please watch this website and your email as campus updates emerge.        How to Request an Appointment on UICcareers.com     How to Request an Appointment on UICcareers.com         how to   To request an appointment, login to your UICcareers.com account. In addition to scheduling career advising appointments through UICcareers.com, you can also search and apply for internships, full-time jobs, and on-campus jobs. Please note the Engineering Career Center does not provide academic (class) advising services.   If it is your first time logging into UICcareers.com, please select “forgot password” to create your password.  If this is your first time logging into UICcareers.com, you will need to create a basic student profile before the system will allow you to schedule an appointment.  Select “Calendar and Appointments” on the left sidebar.  Click “Counseling Appt” on the top of the page. If you do not see this option, please email Eliana Riley at eliana@uic.edu  Click “Request New Appointment.”  Select the type of appointment from the list provided.  Select the 30-minute time range, coach(es), and day of the week you’d like to schedule your appointment.  Selecting all of the career coaches assigned to you will help you find the best time that works for your schedule.  Your career career coach will either approve your appointment through UICcareers.com and you will receive an email notification letting you know if your appointment was approved.  If you need to cancel your appointment, or reschedule your appointment time, please do so through UICcareers.com at least 24 hours before your scheduled appointment.  If you are an alum who no longer has access to your UICcareers.com account, please email the advisor designated for your major. Click here to see a list of advisors by major.             Schedule Appointment  Log into UICcareers.com       Need support beyond your job search?          Career Tools    Back to main content           Resume    Cover Letter    Searching    Professional Introduction & Connections    LinkedIn    Interviewing    Following Up & Thank You Messages    Offers & Salary    Schedule an Appointment                  UIC Logo        Engineering Career Center       Contact   851 S. Morgan St. | 800 SEO | Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: (312) 996-8374  rcconroy@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    LinkedIn    Twitter    Instagram            UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veteran